#   Chance Field
Throw 2 dices (Tell which one is ! And 2)

|Dice1|Dice 2|Event

| 1	| 1-2	 |Advance to GO 

| 1	| 3-4	|Advance to MCAFEE Street. if you pass Go, collect $1000.

| 1	| 5-6	|Advance to Wassa Street. If you pass Go, collect $1000. Pay the owner double the amount usual. You can buy it, if not owned
 
| 2	| 1-2 |Advance token to the nearest Railroad and pay owner twice the rental to which he/she  is otherwise entitled. If Railroad is unowned, you may buy it from the Bank. (There are 2 of these.)

| 2	| 3-4	|Advance token to the nearest Railroad and pay owner twice the rental to which he/she  is otherwise entitled. If Railroad is unowned, you may buy it from the Bank.

| 2	| 5-6 | Advance token to nearest Utility. If unowned, you may buy it from the Bank. If owned, throw dice and pay owner a total 10 (ten) times the amount thrown.

| 3	| 1-2 |Advance to "Go".

| 3	| 3-4 | Bank pays you dividend of $5000.

| 3	| 5-6 | Get out of Jail Free. (take card)

| 4	| 1-2 | Get out of Jail Free. (take card)

| 4	| 3-4 | Go Back Three  Spaces

# UNI drop


Take all the money from the middle area
If there is no money in the middle area, since noone paid yet or it was just taken out...
Put 500$ into the middle area!

| 4 | 5-6 Make general repairs on all your property: For each house pay $25, For each hotel {pay} $100.

| 5 | 1-2 | Pay poor tax of $100

| 5 | 3-4 | Take a ride to King’s Cross Station. If you pass Go, collect $1000.

| 5 | 5-6 | Take a walk on the Boardwalk. Advance token to BTC Street.

|6 | 1-2 | Your building {and} loan matures. Receive {Collect} $1500
 
| 6 | 3-4 | You have won a crossword competition. Collect $1000

| 6 | 5-6 | Get free out of jail (take a card)

# Common field
Throw 2 dices (tell which one is dice1 and which one is dice2 before)
|Dice1|Dice2| Event

| 1 | 1-2 | Bank error in your favor. Collect $1000. 

| 1 | 3-4 | Doctor's fees. {fee} Pay $500.

| 1 | 5-6 | From sale of stock you get $500. 

| 2 | 1-2 | Get Out of Jail Free (take a card).

| 2 | 3-4 | Go to Jail. Go directly to jail. Do not pass Go, Do not collect $1000.
  
| 2 | 5-6 | Grand Opera Night. Collect $500 from every player for opening night seats. 

| 3 | 1-2 | Holiday  Fund matures. Receive  $1000. 

| 3 | 3-4 | Income tax refund. Collect $200.

| 3 | 5-6 | It is your birthday. Collect $100 from every player.

| 4 | 1-2 | Life insurance matures – Collect $1000 

| 4 | 3-4 | Hospital Fees. Pay $500. 

| 4 | 5-6 | School fees. Pay $500. 

| 5 | 1-2 | Receive $300 consultancy fee. 

| 5 | 3-4 | You are assessed for street repairs: Pay $40 per house and $115 per hotel you own. 

| 5 | 5-6 | You have won second prize in a beauty contest. Collect $100. 

| 6 | 1-2 | You inherit $1000. 

| 6 | 3-4 | Gas fee raised pay 1000$

| 6 | 5-6 | Roll again
d

# How to play
# Press M to move stuff
Press R to replicate money from the bank
Everyone starts with 25,000$ 

Choose a Voxable with its colour squarses.

You put one of your colour square in front of a street, when you bought it.

If you buy a house or hotel, you need to put them in front of the street aswell.

A house cost the same amount as the street price. A hotel costs 4 houses + street price.
# Rent
The specific rent price of a street is multiplied by the following values, if buildings are on it.

1 house:   5x | 1 hotel:  100x

2 houses: 15x | 2 hotels: 200x

3 houses: 30x | 3 hotels: 300x

4 houses  50x | 4 hotels: 400x

# Buy 2000
# Rent: 250
If the owner has more than 1 station the rent is multiplied with the amount of  them
eg. 3 stations = 3x
